text.tspan: One of the core plot points in Arcane is the Powder to Jinx transformation, where Powder lets
her innocent self die and adapts the last thing her sister calls her by—Jinx— before they get
separated upon the accident of her killing half of her family.
Vi remains unaware of this transformation until Caitlyn breaks her out of prison. However, even
after she learns of it, she still believes Powder is still in there and calls or mentions her as that
throughout the last arc, including The Monster You Created. This causes Powder's mentions
count to remain the same across both the first and final episodes, despite Powder not really
being there anymore. Powder's mention count is shown as a perfectly horizontal line indicating
that in the spline chart.

text.data-name: On the contrary, Jinx is only mentioned once in Welcome to the Playground. This mention appears to be also the first time Powder is ever described as Jinx. It is when Vi calls her Jinx for the second time just before she leaves that Powder adapts it as her
text.tspan: On the contrary, Jinx is only mentioned once in Welcome to the Playground. This mention
appears to be also the first time Powder is ever described as Jinx. It is when Vi calls her Jinx
for the second time just before she leaves that Powder adapts it as her new self and thus
becomes The Monster You —Vi— created. While Mylo referring to her as Jinx in the first
episode doesn't phase her, unlike Vi's opinion, it is what sat the ground for the second time
later on and thus remains the true beginning.
As Powder transforms into Jinx, Jinx mentions increase to 11 in The Monster You Created. We
also see Jinx taking more space than Powder with almost twice as many lines, indicating how
she is more confident as Jinx than little shy Powder. This also reflects what we see in the
show; Powder is desperate to be helpful and feels less "than half the person" Vi was at her
age. Meanwhile, Jinx keeps creating advanced deadly weapons and is second in command of
her new team.
